{{Infobox newspaper | name = BizWest | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | motto = | type = Monthly | format = | owner = BizWest Media | founder = Jeff Nuttall and Chris Wood | publisher = Jeff Nuttall and Chris Wood | editor = Chris Wood | maneditor = Ken Amundson | staff = 4 | foundation = <!-- or |launched= --> <!-- Use: {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | language = English | headquarters = | publishing_city = Boulder, Colorado | publishing_country = United States | circulation = | circulation_date = | circulation_ref = | readership = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = 2334-5721 | website = {{URL|bizwest.com}} }}
'''''BizWest''''' is a [[print media|print]] and [[Digital media|electronic]] [[List of business newspapers|business paper]] in [[Northern Colorado]].
== History == In 2010, [[Brown Publishing Company]], the owner of the newspapers ''Boulder County Business Report'' and ''Northern Colorado Business Report'' declared bankruptcy and, in September, sold them to [[Ohio Community Media]]. In February 2011, the publishers of the two papers formed BizWest Media to acquire their publications, the ''Wyoming Business Report'', and ancillary other assets from Ohio Community Media.<ref>{{cite news |title=Publisher-led group buys Colorado business newspapers |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/denver/news/2011/02/13/bcbr.html |newspaper=[[Denver Business Journal]] |date=February 13, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Wallace |first=Alicia |date=February 14, 2011 |title=Boulder publishing company acquires Boulder County Business Report |newspaper=[[The Daily Camera]]}}</ref> In March 2014, the ''Boulder County Business Report'' and ''Northern Colorado Business Report'' were merged into a biweekly printed paper called ''BizWest'', with initial circulation of 9,000 to cover [[Boulder County, Colorado|Boulder]], [[Broomfield County|Broomfield]], [[Larimer County, Colorado|Larimer]] and [[Weld County, Colorado|Weld counties]], as well as the Denver-Boulder corridor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coloradoan.com/story/money/2014/02/26/noco-biz-report-to-form-bizwest-with-denver-publication/5848351/|title=Northern Colorado Business Report to form BizWest with Denver publication |newspaper=[[Fort Collins Coloradoan]] |date=February 26, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.denverpost.com/2014/02/26/colorado-business-papers-combine-into-biweekly-newspaper-bizwest/ |title=Colorado business papers combine into biweekly newspaper BizWest |last= |first= |date=26 February 2014 |website=[[The Denver Post]] |publisher=Digital First Media |access-date=25 October 2017 |quote=}}</ref>
In September 2016, ''BizWest'' reduced its print publication frequency to monthly and laid off four of its eighteen staff, including one writer. The company cited subscribers shifting to digital-only subscriptions and management's desire to focus on growth areas of the business as reasons for the changes.<ref>{{cite news |last=Castle |first=Shay |date=September 14, 2016 |title=BizWest lays off 4, shifts to once-monthly print schedule |url=http://www.dailycamera.com/boulder-business/ci_30361283/bizwest-lays-off-4-shifts-once-monthly-print |newspaper=[[The Daily Camera]]}}</ref>
