'''Ernest Alfred Adams''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|OBE|size=85%}} (23 November 1892 &ndash; 29 August 1976) was a New Zealand baker, businessman and philanthropist. He was born in [[Wellington]], [[Somerset]], England.<ref name="DNZB Adams">{{DNZB|title=Ernest Alfred Adams|first= Sarah|last= Adams|id=5a4|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> He co-founded Ernest Adams Limited.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teara.govt.nz/en/biographies/5a4/adams-ernest-alfred|title=Adams, Ernest Alfred|publisher=Te Ara|accessdate=7 May 2013}}</ref>

In the [[1962 Birthday Honours|1962 Queen's Birthday Honours]], Adams was appointed an [[Order of the British Empire|Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] for services to the community, especially in social welfare work.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=42685 |date=2 June 1962 |page=4348 |supp=y }}</ref>

