{{other people|John Drummond}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=November 2016}}
'''John Drummond''' (1676 – 20 December 1742)<ref>{{rayment-hc|p|1|date=July 2014}}</ref> was a Scottish banker, merchant and politician.

He was the third son George Drummond of [[Blair Drummond]], Perthshire, and his wife Elizabeth, daughter of [[Sir Gilbert Ramsay, 1st Baronet]], from [[Bamff]] in Perthshire.<ref name="histparl-john-drummond-d1742" />

In 1691 he moved to [[Amsterdam]], where he became a successful merchant and banker. There he met and befriended [[James Brydges, 1st Duke of Chandos|James Brydges]] (later [[Duke of Chandos]]), who assisted his career thereafter.<ref name="histparl-john-drummond-d1742" />

He was the [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) for [[Perth Burghs (UK Parliament constituency)|Perth Burghs]] from 1727 until his death in 1742.<ref name="histparl-john-drummond-d1742" />

