'''Peter Askin''' (Born 1940) is an actor, director, producer and screenwriter best known for directing the 2007 film ''[[Trumbo (2007 film)|Trumbo]]'', a documentary about the Oscar-winning Hollywood screenwriter [[Dalton Trumbo]] who was [[blacklist]]ed for being a member of the [[Hollywood Ten]].<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news|last=Cieply|first=Michael|title=A Voice From the Blacklist: Documentary Lets Dalton Trumbo Speak (Through Surrogates)|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/09/11/movies/11trumbo.html?_r=1&oref=slogin|accessdate=December 15, 2011|newspaper=New York Times|date=September 11, 2007}}</ref> For the film, he worked closely with Trumbo's son, [[Christopher Trumbo]].<ref name=pbs>{{cite web|title=Dalton Trumbo - Interview with Director Peter Askin|url=https://www.pbs.org/wnet/americanmasters/episodes/dalton-trumbo/interview-with-director-peter-askin/1167/|publisher=PBS|accessdate=December 16, 2001}}</ref>
==Biography== Born to a [[American Jews|Jewish]] family,<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/25/theater/theater-sex-even-love-whatever-it-takes-to-connect.html New York Times: "THEATER; Sex, Even Love, Whatever It Takes to Connect" By JOHN LEGUIZAMO] November 25, 2001</ref> Askin is the son of Alma Askin, the daughter of [[Joseph Durst]],<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2002/04/22/classified/paid-notice-deaths-askin-alma.html New York Times: "Paid Notice: Deaths ASKIN, ALMA"] April 22, 2002</ref> the founder of the [[Durst Organization]] and member of one of the most prominent real estate families in New York City in the 20th century.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/09/nyregion/09families.html?_r=0 New York Times: "In City Real Estate, Old Clans Are Shrewd Again" By CHARLES V. BAGLI] February 8, 2010</ref> He was educated at [[Middlebury College]] and [[Columbia University]].<ref name=EnterPlayMakers>Hischak, Thomas S. [https://books.google.com/books?id=DCTUkTpL8V8C&pg=PA7&lpg=PA7&dq=Peter+Askin+Down+an+Alley+Filled+with+Cats&source=bl&ots=FQF0MsXKgm&sig=6qca9jRsy7MUkGu7p-WaMgx_6Og&hl=en&sa=X&ei=wly2U5j1KYSlyAS7tIDYBQ&ved=0CDQQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=askin&f=false Enter the Playmakers: Directors and Choreographers on the New York Stage] 2006</ref> He trained under [[Wynn Handman]] at the American Place Theater in New York City.<ref name=EnterPlayMakers /> Askin made his debut in 1986 with ''Down an Alley Filled with Cats.''<ref name=EnterPlayMakers /> Askin was the screenwriter for such films as ''[[Company Man (film)|Company Man]]'' (which he also co-directed) and ''[[Smithereens (film)|Smithereens]]'', and he directed and produced the musical ''[[Hedwig and the Angry Inch (musical)|Hedwig and the Angry Inch]]''.<ref name=broadway>{{cite web|title=Hedwig and the Angry Inch|url=http://www.lortel.org/LLA_archive/index.cfm?search_by=show&id=374|publisher=The Internet Off-Broadway Database|accessdate=December 16, 2011}}</ref>
